get.description:
# Status: ‚úî

## ‚ö° About
This Endpoint exctracts all the necessary data for a Module to function.

It returns a Model of type [Environment](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Environment#status-).

The information is used to:
- Set App Global Vars
- Set the Module Vars
- Get the necessary DSL information

## üéØ Path Parameters

 - üÉè DSLUID
   - 0 / Empty = Default DSL (taken from Project > GlobalVars > DLSDefault)
   - Any other value = UID of the DSL to be loaded.
 
 - üÉè MODULE
   - MAP = Requesting environment info for [MAP Module](https://github.com/TheIOFoundation/ProjectLockdown/tree/master/MAP)
   - BO = Requesting environment info for [BO Module](https://github.com/TheIOFoundation/ProjectLockdown/tree/master/BO)
   - API = Requesting environment info for [API Module](https://github.com/TheIOFoundation/ProjectLockdown/tree/master/API)

- üÉè EnvironmenUID
  - 0 = Default App configuration
  - Any other value = Custom environment configurations, for instance custom environments for Users (User Preferences).


## üì¢ Invoked by
- [MAP](https://github.com/TheIOFoundation/ProjectLockdown/tree/master/MAP)
- üìë [BO](https://github.com/TheIOFoundation/ProjectLockdown/tree/master/BO)
- üìë [API](https://github.com/TheIOFoundation/ProjectLockdown/tree/master/API)

# Status: ‚úî

## ‚ö° About
An Environment object represents the collection of data that is necessary for a Module to function.

It is composed by 2 main objects:
- [Project](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Project) global variables
- [DataSet Layer](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/DataSetLayer) to be rendered in the Module

It also includes a number of [Statistics](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Stat) that can be used to present information to the user.

# Status: üöß

## ‚ö° About  
A DataSet Layer object represents the collection of data that defines a DSL in Project Lockdown. A DSL is a collection of [DataPoints](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/DataPoint) (DP) that are selected to track the impact of a specific family of policies over a specific Human or Digital Right.

It is composed by üìë:



It also includes a number of [Statistics](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Stat) that can be used to present information to the user.
üìë Listing of Stats & their definitions


## üì¢ Used by
- üìë ???

## üîó URL fields
- URLDocs: Permalink to the documentation explaining this DSL.
- URLDSL: Permalink for this DSL.
- URLDEI: Permalink to the DEI for this DSL.
- URLMethodology: Permalink providing Methodology information for the DSL.
- üìë URLAPI: Permalink providing access to the API serving this DSL.
- URLSchema: Permalink providing access to the Schema forming this DSL.
- üìë URLQALog: Permalink providing access to the QA log for the DSL.
- URLLicense: Permalink providing Licensing information for the DSL.
- URLCitingPolicy: Permalink providing Citing information for the DSL.

## üìÖ Date Fields
- DateFirstPublished: First time this DSL was published.
   üìë Note: Maybe we put this in Log too?
- DateLastUpdated: Last Date and Time the DSL was updated.
   üìë Note: Maybe we put this in Log too?
- DateUpdatedNext: Next scheduled Date and Time the DSL will be updated.
- DateFirstDay: First Day (Left limit) considered in the DSL.
- DateLastDay: Last Day (Right limit) considered in the DSL.

## ‚ùì DUBIOUS FIELDS
- DateTimeFormat
- UpdatedFreq: Scheduled frequency for updates on the DSL, in milliseconds.
- MethodologyCode: Extra information inside the Methodology.
- üìë AccessLevel: Indicates the access conditions for this DSL
- LicenseCode: Extra information inside the Licensing.
- CitingPolicyCode: Extra information inside the Citing.

Snapshot.description:
# Status: üëÅÔ∏è‚Äçüó®Ô∏è

## ‚ö° About
A Snapshot is represents the individual, daily value of a datapoint. They are used to render the datapoint's value on MAP in a sinple and efficient way, avoiding complex and resource comsiming calculations in the client.

Snapshots are stored in Answer objects. This allows to reuse the same Model for both RAW and Snapshot data since there is no difference between both.
For more information about RAW and Snapshot data, see the diagram below.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9198668/104857302-69abf700-5952-11eb-9918-93a6736af696.png)
‚ùì >> Make proper diagram


## üåê Expanded information
More information about Snapshots can be found on the 

## Snapshot generation
Snapshots can be generated in a number of ways.


üî∂ **Deduced** - Generated by applying some sort of methodology over the DSE data to extract a pattern that is relevant. This type of snapshot is generated by a PLD script based on the data obtained from all the üì¶ [DataSet Entry](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/DataSetEntry) in a üì¶ [DataSet Layer](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/DataSetLayer) or from the **Encoded Snapshopt** data from an external 3rd party (see below).

**Examples**
- COVID-19 NPIs: Military presence policy without DateEnd
- COVID-19 NPIs: Schools closed for over 3 months

‚ñ∂ **Snapshot example from PLD DSL RAW data**: A RAW datapoint encoded with an üì¶[Answer](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Answer) like this 
```
- Answer
  - Type: "RAW" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Funnel:IS"
  - Value: "3"
  - DateStart: "01/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "03/01/2020'
```
would generate a Snapshot encoded with an üì¶[Answer](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Answer) like this 
```
- Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: Snapshot"
  - Value: "3"
  - DateStart: "01/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "01/01/2020"

- Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: Snapshot"
  - Value: "3"
  - DateStart: "02/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "02/01/2020"

- Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: Snapshot"
  - Value: "3"
  - DateStart: "03/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "03/01/2020"
```

‚ñ∂ **Snapshot example from a 3rd party ENDCODED Snapshot data** (see below): 
Following the example indicated above, a Snapshot encoded with an [Answer](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Answer) like this (which was obtained from a 3rd party 
```
- Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: API"
  - Value: "125.000"
  - DateStart: "01/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "01/01/2020'
 
 - Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: API"
  - Value: "147.000"
  - DateStart: "02/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "02/01/2020'
 
  - Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: API"
  - Value: "152.000"
  - DateStart: "03/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "03/01/2020'
```
would generate a Snapshot encoded with an üì¶[Answer](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Answer) like this 
```
- Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: Snapshot"
  - Value: "0"
  - DateStart: "01/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "01/01/2020"

- Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: Snapshot"
  - Value: "1"
  - DateStart: "02/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "02/01/2020"

- Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: Snapshot"
  - Value: "0"
  - DateStart: "03/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "03/01/2020"
```


üî∂ **Encoded** - Generated by a PLD script out of data obtained from 3rd party sources, typically APIs. This is used to translate 3rd party data in a format that can be easily processed by MAP.

**Examples**
- World population by territory
- COVID-19 declared cases

**Snapshot example**
A 3rd party segment of data encoded like this 
```
- Country
  - Name: Malaysia 
  - Year: 2019
  - Population: 43.000.000
```
would generate a Snapshot encoded with an üì¶[Answer](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Answer) like this 
```
- Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot" 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: API"
  - Value: "43.000.000"
  - DateStart: "01/01/2020"
  - DateEnd: "01/01/2020"
 
 [...]
 
- Answer
  - Type: "Snapshot' 
  - GeneratedBy: "Algorithm: API"
  - Value: "43.000.000"
  - DateStart: "31/12/2020"
  - DateEnd: "31/12/2020"
```

## SourceTypes and Snapshots
Each üì¶[DataSet Layer](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/DataSetLayer) has a list of approved üì¶[SourceType](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/SourceType) from which data is extracted to generate the RAW data for its datapoints.

‚ùó Each SourceType generates its own Snapshot per dataproint.
This is represented in the SourceTypeUID field.


## ‚öô Generating Snapshots ‚ùì

**Recalculating Snapshots** can be done
- Triggered on the spot
- Scheduled
- Scheduled with execution triggered by some flag or a pending queue

**General Snapshot generation**
- Each DSL has a FirstDate and and LastDate
- When creating a new DSL, all DPs get a Snapshot PER SourceType that is initialized.
- Compression applied(?)
- When a new DP is entered for a specific SourceType then
    - All such snapshots are recalculated
- When a new DP is entered with StartDate < FirstDate then
    - All Snapshots of that DSL are expanded "to the left"
    - FirstDate = StartDate
    - All such snapshots are recalculated
- When a new DP is entered with LastDate < EndDate then
    - All Snapshots of that DSL are expanded "to the right"
    - LastDate = EndDate 
    - All such snapshots are recalculated

Note: 
We need to look into compression while being able to filter PER DATE RANGE unless we download ALL the range since it would be compressed.

## üì¢ Used by
This Model is used in the following modules through these Endpoints:
- MAP
    - üí† [Environments](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/paths/~1Environments~1%7BDSLUID%7D~1%7BModule%7D~1%7BEnvironmentUID%7D/get)
    (Indirecly)

## üîó URL fields
- URLCodebase: Perrmalink to the code where this snapshot is generated.

## üìÖ Date Fields
- DateFirstCreated: Date and time when the Snapshot was generated for the first time.
- DateLastUpdated: Date and time when the Snapshot was last generated.

## ‚ö° About
An Date object represents the collection of data that is necessary to establish a _date & time_ and to describe its function.

Dates can be generated though one of the several [Funnels](https://github.com/TheIOFoundation/ProjectLockdown/tree/master/Funnels) and according to transparent algorithms (see üìë documentation).

üî• The actual Date value is stored in üìë XXX format in 2 different fields:
- Value: As entered via [Funnel](https://github.com/TheIOFoundation/ProjectLockdown/tree/master/Funnels)
- valueUTC: Converted to UTC (GMT+0), which enables a properly referenced timeline of events.

The Type field indicates what kind of information the Link points to:

üìë

## ‚ö° About  
A DataSet Entry object represents the collection of data points extracted from a Source for a given DSL. A DSL is a collection of [DataPoints](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/DataPoint) (DP) that are selected to track the impact of a specific family of policies over a specific Human or Digital Right.



It is composed by üìë:


It also includes a number of [Statistics](https://theiofoundation.stoplight.io/docs/projectlockdown/API/Reference/Project-Lockdown.v1.json/components/schemas/Stat) that can be used to present information to the user.
üìë Listing of Stats & their definitions

## ‚ùó Important
One source can be the origin of different DSEs as it may contain policies that are monitored in separate DSLs.
